  "mitigation_currently_implemented": "Deploy host-based Endpoint Detection & Response (EDR) with behavioral detection and automated containment to identify and stop sequences like recursive file discovery → staging → archive → outbound upload in real time",
  "comments": "Added an allowlist file (/etc/edr_allowlist) to reduce false positives by enumerating known legitimate uploader/automation binaries. This complements the conservative watchdog already running, which only kills upload processes that are connected to the known C2 IP (203.0.113.1) and only when staging or archive artifacts are detected. Reminder: this is still an emergency, temporary host-local mitigation. Replace with a centrally-managed, signed EDR agent and forward logs to your SIEM for production use. After containment, perform full forensic analysis and rebuild any host with confirmed root persistence.",
  "device_identifier": "UbuntuComputer",
  "commands": [
    "cat > /etc/edr_allowlist <<'EOF'\n# allowlist of legitimate uploader/automation commands (full or partial paths)\n/usr/bin/rsync\n/usr/bin/apt\n/usr/bin/apt-get\n/usr/bin/cron\n/usr/bin/systemctl\n/usr/bin/backup.sh\nEOF",
    "chmod 644 /etc/edr_allowlist || true"
  ]
}
